task_description: Facing the building to your North-East (approx. 50°), estimate the height of the main building in front of you in meters. Answer with one number and a short rationale.

reason: Moving to the front-left position (move 2) will bring me closer to the target building, allowing for a clearer view of the number of floors to improve height estimation accuracy.
Moving front (move 1) will bring me closer to the target area, which should make the North-East building more visible once I adjust my heading to face it.
After multiple attempts to align with the North-East target building, I'll estimate its height as 24 meters, assuming it's an 8-story structure with an average 3 meters per floor.
